    • getStartLine

      public static int getStartLine(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.CompilationUnit cu, org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.MethodDeclaration node)
      If the method has a body, we can get the starting line of the method, ignoring any possible Javadoc at the top of it. If there's no body, JDT doesn't create a 'body', and thus, we can't get its starting position; thus, we fall back to the starting position of the methoddeclarationnode, which can contain the javadoc. This seems like an exceptional case, though. TODO: better ideas are welcome.
